\subsection{OpenCV Preprocessing Performance}
The image processing layer\cite{opencv2024} proved highly effective in neutralizing real-world variance from informal drawings. The stabilization executes perfectly across a strict sequence:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Raw Sketch Ingestion:} Captures the varied, noisy user inputs natively from the browser\cite{chen2019}.
    \item \textbf{Grayscale Conversion:} Flattens all color channels to isolate pure structural intent\cite{opencv2024}.
    \item \textbf{Adaptive Gaussian Thresholding:} Neutralizes uneven ambient lighting and severe paper shadows instantly\cite{opencv2024}.
    \item \textbf{Canny Edge Detection:} Identifies stark geometric boundary lines with high-precision thresholding mechanisms\cite{canny1986}.
    \item \textbf{Morphological Transformations:} Successfully bridges and closes the empty gaps present in faint, hand-drawn lines to yield a stabilized binary tensor signal\cite{opencv2024}.
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{U-Net Semantic Segmentation}
The integration of a singular, unified U-Net model\cite{ronneberger2015} demonstrated exceptional capability in isolating structural wall regions natively from the background, eliminating the need for disjointed sub-networks. Evaluated purely on structural logic and boundary coherence without rigid numerical penalties, the unified model processed complex inputs robustly:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Contextual Wall Recognition:} Distinguishes intentional structural strokes from random sketch noise reliably, without requiring manual algorithmic recalibration\cite{ronneberger2015, chen2019}.
    \item \textbf{Spatial Localization:} The localized skip-connections\cite{ronneberger2015} flawlessly maintain the physical proportions of the rooms during deep matrix inference.
    \item \textbf{Clean Vectorization:} The resulting binary predictions seamlessly transition into pure machine coordinates via clean contour extraction algorithms\cite{douglas1973, liu2017}.
\end{itemize}


